name: National Dog Show
summary: The National Dog Show, an annual Thanksgiving tradition, will be available for viewing on various platforms. To watch, tune in to NBC at 12 pm EST or stream it live on Peacock or fuboTV. The event features over 200 dog breeds competing for the Best in Show title. This year, a new breed, the Mudi, will make its debut. The show has a rich history and has been a beloved pastime for many years, with various dog breeds winning top honors in the past. One notable winner is Vito the Pug, who recently made history as the first of his breed to win Best in Show at the 2024 event.

name: David Montgomery
summary: Multiple news outlets report that Detroit Lions running backs David Montgomery and Amon-Ra St. Brown are expected to play in the Thanksgiving Day game against the Chicago Bears. Montgomery has been dealing with a shoulder injury, but he returned to practice on Wednesday and was listed as questionable for the game. St. Brown has not been on the injury report. The two players have been compared to the video game characters Sonic and Knuckles, with Montgomery being the speedy and agile Sonic and St. Brown being the strong and powerful Knuckles. Fantasy football experts and analysts have praised Montgomery's performance this season, highlighting his recent success in Week 12.

name: Manchester United
summary: Manchester United drew their first Premier League match under new manager Ruben Amorim, tying 2-2 with Ipswich Town. Despite the result, experts are optimistic about Amorim's potential to improve the team's performance. In his debut European match, United narrowly defeated Bodo/Glimt 3-2 in the Europa League. Coverage of Amorim's first game as United manager includes analysis of the starting lineup, live streams of the Ipswich match, and predictions for future matches. One notable observation is that Amorim believes United players were overly cautious in the Ipswich game, suggesting that he may emphasize a more aggressive approach in the future.
